April 29 – May 3, 2026 • Ambergris Caye, Belize

Celebrating Angie’s 50th

Sun, reef, and friends. Everything you need is below for this 4‑night trip — hotel, flights, golf carts, and a snorkel tour.

RSVP & Tour Interest Trip Hotel

Trip Hotel

Coco Beach Resort (Sandy Point Resorts)

Upscale beachfront resort with large pools and a swim‑up bar; north of San Pedro.

Additional Hotel Option

Belizean Shores Resort

Condo‑style suites with pool and beach access in the same area.

Getting There

Fly to Belize City (BZE). Multiple airlines serve BZE; however, American Airlines offers the quickest route to Belize.

Hop Flight to San Pedro (Tropic Air)

Book once in Belize after getting through Customs/Immigration. 15‑minute flight to Ambergris Caye.

Additional Option: Maya Island Air

Alternate domestic hop between BZE & San Pedro with frequent departures.

Golf Cart Rentals

Primary way to get around San Pedro. Reserve ahead for best rates.

Isla Bonita Golf Cart Rentals

Airport‑adjacent; online booking and published rates.

VIP Golf Cart Rental

Well‑reviewed operator; south of town.

C&S Golf Cart Rentals

Delivers to resorts; 4‑ & 6‑seaters.

Optional Tour

Hol Chan Marine Reserve + Shark Ray Alley (Snorkel)

Belize’s iconic snorkel with coral gardens, turtles, nurse sharks & rays. Great for all levels.

Belize Pro Dive Center  •  Tuff E Nuff
